  "title": "Director (Asia-Pacific Department , Governance Planning Team)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your\nkey roles & responsibilities include:</strong>  </p><p>·      Supporting and coordinating overseas offices of Asia-Pacific in the business area of Japanese and Non-Japanese Corporate Banking.</p><p>·      Communicating with offices in this region, other overseas regions and Japan for the promotion of the Japanese and Non-Japanese Corporate Banking business.</p><p>·      Promoting business to achieve the targets of each Branch and supporting the enhancement of governance.</p><p>·      Preparing and submitting reports to managements in Asia-Pacific and Japan (Head office) in both English and Japanese language.<br /></p><p><strong>What you should have:  </strong></p><p>·        A Bachelor's degree.</p><p>·        At least 16 years of experience in banking industry and corporate finance.</p><p>·        Strong understanding of a wide range of banking products such as corporate loans and transaction banking products is required.</p><p>·        The ability to work in a team as well as strong verbal and written communication skills are attributes which will help the candidate perform well in this role.</p><p>·        Business-level proficiency in English and as you are required to communicate, read and understand as well as respond and present to managements in Asia-Pacific and Japan (Head office).</p><p>·        Strong understanding and affiliation to Japanese financial industry with relevant network.</p>",
